# Arrow Responsiveness Improvement Walkthrough

## Summary of Changes
We have significantly improved the responsiveness of the indoor navigation arrow, both visually and logically, when the user turns.

1. **Visual Responsiveness (MapScreen)**
   - The user avatar's directional arrow now reads directly from the real-time gyroscope heading instead of the step-delayed Particle Filter state. This ensures that the arrow spins instantly and smoothly as you rotate the device.

2. **Logical Turn Sensitivity (Config)**
   - Lowered the `TURN_ANGLE_THRESHOLD` from `30` degrees to `15` degrees in [navigationConfig.ts](file:///c:/Code/project/New%20folder/indoor-nav-app/src/config/navigationConfig.ts). The system is now much more sensitive to **微小的转弯** (micro turns).

3. **Instant State Solidification (Engine)**
   - Modified `ParticleFilter.handleTurnEvent` to immediately compute and return the new [PFState](file:///c:/Code/project/New%20folder/indoor-nav-app/src/engine/ParticleFilter.ts#30-46) (including particle weights and position).
   - `NavigationEngine.handleTurn` now actively digests this updated [PFState](file:///c:/Code/project/New%20folder/indoor-nav-app/src/engine/ParticleFilter.ts#30-46) and rewrites its internal navigation state instantly, rather than waiting for the next physical step to reflect the new direction.

## Validation Status
✅ **Fast Refresh Updated**: The expo server running in the background will have already synced these changes to your device via Fast Refresh.

## Manual Verification
Try the following on your device to verify:
1. Tap a start and destination node on the map and hit "Navigate".
2. **Stand perfectly still** and simply rotate your phone. The blue directional arrow should spin instantaneously.
3. Make a small turn (~15-20 degrees). You should see the `↪️ Turn Detected!` indicator appear much faster than before.
